<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<FindBugsFilter xmlns="https://github.com/spotbugs/filter/3.0.0">
  <!--
    Reviewed suppressions (Chapter 16: suppress with a reason, never disable a whole detector).

    This module ships ONE deliberate counter-example, InconsistentlySyncedCounter, whose
    inconsistent-synchronization finding is the chapter's teaching point: SpotBugs reports the unguarded
    read of a field that every write holds a lock for as IS2_INCONSISTENT_SYNC (the MT_CORRECTNESS
    category), and Error Prone's @GuardedBy check rejects the same access at compile time. The class
    exists precisely so the build SEES that shape, so the finding is expected, not a defect to fix in
    place — the narrowly-scoped suppression below keeps the `quality` build green while leaving the
    detector fully on for every other class. The fix the chapter recommends (guard every access, or make
    the field an AtomicLong) lives in GuardedCounter, which carries no suppression because it has no
    finding. A genuine, unreviewed finding anywhere else still fails the build.
  -->
  <Match>
    <Class name="org.acme.vthreads.InconsistentlySyncedCounter"/>
    <Bug pattern="IS2_INCONSISTENT_SYNC"/>
  </Match>
</FindBugsFilter>
